headline.main: DR. GEORGE E. HALE, ASTRONOMER, DEAD; Founder of Yerkes, Mt. Wilson and Palomar Observatories Is Stricken at 69 MADE IMPORTANT PHOTOS Discoverer of Magnetic Fields in Sunspots--Copley Medal Among Many Honors Became III a Year Ago Praised by Dr. Carrel Received Many Honors

snippet: Dr. George Ellery Hale, one of the world's most renowned astronomers, died of heart trouble today in the Las Encinas Sanitarium. He was 69 years old, born In Chicago June 29, 1868.

byline.original: Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES
